ROOTS OF A RED COLOUR.

The Guaranies in marshy places dig up roots called yzipb with a dusky surface, which they use to dye woollen, and cotton cloths of a dark red. Whether this root be the rubia of dyers I cannot venture to affirm, for though that plant is cultivated in Austria‚ I never happened to see it.
